{"about": "I am an open source enthusiast who derives great joy from simple and elegant solutions: the command-line ecosystem, short algorithms, the tldr program, the AeroPress. In the name of simple solutions, I've learned a great deal about data science and system design to solve old problems in more interesting ways.

Many of those old problems are the daily annoyances faced as a Linux fan. I’m in the midst of solving 17 of them with ML-based open source software, which I’ve documented in my blog in research-style articles. Designing these solutions has made me very comfortable starting from hazy requirements, exploring (often poorly documented) codebases, and doing so self-sufficiently. 

My experience as a data science intern then made me effective in the work environment. I thought I was training the models to be predictive, but instead the models were training me to be resourceful! {"about": "Hi, I’m a student at Georgia Tech's Scheller College of Business pursuing a Information Technology focused Bachelor of Science in Business Administration!  I have interests in consulting, software development, supply chain management, and data analytics.

Over the past two summers, I’ve had the opportunity to dive into data analytics and project management, working as an intern at Southern Green Industries.
